Paper: hep-th/0009195

Date: 2000-09-25

Title: Gravitationally bound monopoles

Authors: Betti Hartmann (U. Oldenburg), Burkhard Kleihaus (U. College Dublin)

and Jutta Kunz (U. Oldenburg)Comments: 8 pages, 4 Postscript figures,section on black holes added

Journal-ref: Phys.Rev.Lett. 86 (2001) 1422-1425

We construct monopole solutions in SU(2) Einstein-Yang-Mills-Higgs theory,carrying magnetic charge n. For vanishing and small Higgs selfcoupling, thesemultimonopole solutions are gravitationally bound. Their mass per unit chargeis lower than the mass of the n=1 monopole. For large Higgs selfcoupling only arepulsive phase exists.